NAME
    gcloud dns record-sets transaction add - append a record-set addition to
        the transaction

SYNOPSIS
    gcloud dns record-sets transaction add DATA [DATA ...] --name=NAME
        --ttl=TTL --type=TYPE --zone=ZONE, -z ZONE
        [--transaction-file=TRANSACTION_FILE; default="transaction.yaml"]
        [GCLOUD_WIDE_FLAG ...]

DESCRIPTION
    This command appends a record-set addition to the transaction.

POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS
     DATA [DATA ...]
        DNS data (Address/CNAME/MX info, etc.) of the record-set to add.

REQUIRED FLAGS
     --name=NAME
        DNS name of the record-set to add.

     --ttl=TTL
        TTL for the record-set to add.

     --type=TYPE
        Type of the record-set to add.

     --zone=ZONE, -z ZONE
        Name of the managed-zone whose record-sets you want to manage.

OPTIONAL FLAGS
     --transaction-file=TRANSACTION_FILE; default="transaction.yaml"
        Path of the file which contains the transaction.

GCLOUD WIDE FLAGS
    These flags are available to all commands: --account, --configuration,
    --flatten, --format, --help, --log-http, --project, --quiet, --trace-token,
    --user-output-enabled, --verbosity. Run $ gcloud help for details.

EXAMPLES
    To add an A record, run:

        $ gcloud dns record-sets transaction add --zone MANAGED_ZONE \
            --name my.domain. --ttl 1234 \
            --type A "1.2.3.4"

    To add a TXT record with multiple data values, run:

        $ gcloud dns record-sets transaction add --zone MANAGED_ZONE \
            --name my.domain. --ttl 2345 \
            --type TXT "Hello world" "Bye world"

NOTES
    This variant is also available:

        $ gcloud beta dns record-sets transaction add

